metadata.name: Fuel Oil No. 1 (Jet B)
alternate_names: Turbo Fuel B, Jet B Wide-cut; Carburant B de turbo-moteur, Carburéacteur à large gamme de points d’ébullition

reference.reference: Harris, G., The Comparative Toxicity of Crude and Refined Oils to Daphnia Magna, Environment Canada Manuscript Report Number EE-152, Ottawa, Ontario, 29 pp., 1992

metadata.comments: A wide boiling-range petroleum blended from gasoline and kerosene fractions. Operational fuel for many commercial turboprop and turbojet aircraft. For additional fuel specifications refer to ASTM D1655.
